International

     * AquiMob aids system by ComUE d’Aquitaine
     * CAMPUS FRANCE GRANT HOLDERS
     * Eligibility for International University Accommodation
     * How to apply for accommodation in 6 steps
     * Processing your application
     * How to prepare for your arrival ?
     * Disabled accommodation

Processing your application

Drapeau francais

   How is my application processed?

IT’S MY FIRST INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY ACCOMMODATION APPLICATION

   International students applying on an independent basis (not through a
   partnership)

   You receive a first answer as from June:
     * If you receive an accommodation offer: the accommodation
       reservation deadline is indicated on the notification attached to
       the e-mail you have received. To confirm the accommodation
       reservation, you must pay a security deposit before the deadline
       indicated on the notification. Non-observance of the deadline will
       result in the cancellation of the offer and the accommodation will
       be offered to another student. If you have booking problems, you
       must send an email to lodgement.international@crous-bordeaux.fr
       before the deadline.

     * If you don’t receive any accommodation offer: if you still need an
       accommodation in the Aquitaine region, you must confirm your
       application by filling in the waiting list form available on the
       Crous de Bordeaux website from late June. The Crous of Bordeaux
       will carry out allocations depending on availability. If an
       accommodation is available for you, you will be informed by e-mail
       and SMS message

   Important: if you don’t match the eligibility criteria for
   International University Accommodation of Crous de Bordeaux, you could
   not be housed.

   International students taking part in an exchange programme (Erasmus,
   CREPUQ, etc…..)
     * If you receive an accommodation offer in June: the accommodation
       reservation deadline is indicated on the notification attached to
       the e-mail you have received. To confirm the accommodation
       reservation, you must pay a security deposit before the deadline
       indicated on the notification. Non-observance of the deadline will
       result in the cancellation of the offer and the accommodation will
       be offered to another student. If you have booking problems, you
       must send an email to lodgement.international@crous-bordeaux.fr
       before the deadline.

     * If you don’t receive any accommodation offer by the end of June:
       you must contact the international relations office of your host
       institute in France

   Campus France grant holders
     * If you are a Campus France grant holder please consult “Campus
       France grant holders” section


I WISH TO KEEP MY CURRENT UNIVERSITY ACCOMMODATION

     * If you correspond to the university residence readmission criteria,
       you will be notified by e-mail about the renewal of your
       accommodation before the end of May. This notification indicates
       the reservation deadline for your current accommodation (10 €
       security deposit for traditional or renovated accommodation and 30
       € for any other type of accommodation).
     * If you don’t receive an answer by the end of May: you must inform
       the Crous of Bordeaux by e-mail:
       logement.international@crous-bordeaux.fr. If you apply after 31^st
       May, your request will be considered as a late request and not as a
       renewal request: you will have to register on the waiting list by
       the end of June on the Crous of Bordeaux website. If you receive an
       accommodation offer, you will then have to pay the full security
       deposit amount.

   IMPORTANT: If you don’t correspond to university residence readmission
   criteria or if you haven’t applied for an International Student
   Accommodation before the deadline or in case of non-observance of the
   reservation deadline and didn’t send back your rental file to the
   residence file then you will have to leave your accommodation not later
   than 31st August.

   In case of non-readmission, and if you are still occupying an
   accommodation after 31^st August, you will be consider as an
   illegitimate occupant and will be subject to an expulsion procedure.

   SUMMER ACCOMMODATION for students housed in traditional rooms (which
   are normally available for occupation until 30th June):

   Summer accommodation is only possible if the student has reserved their
   accommodation for the start of the following academic year.

   Contact: logement.international@crous-bordeaux.fr

If you didn’t receive any accommodation offer

   Please consult “LOKAVIZ” section

   On this part of the website, you could find private-sector housing ads.

